From: Peios <kernel@peios.org>
Subject: FACS patch 8: deny fallocate mutation modes on append-only fds

fallocate modes PUNCH_HOLE, ZERO_RANGE, COLLAPSE_RANGE, and
INSERT_RANGE mutate existing byte positions without going through
the write path. An fd with FILE_APPEND_DATA but not FILE_WRITE_DATA
must be denied these modes.

Uses the same security_file_deny_pwrite() hook as patches 1-4.

--- a/fs/open.c
+++ b/fs/open.c
@@ -280,6 +280,17 @@
 	if (!(file->f_mode & FMODE_WRITE))
 		return -EBADF;

+	/* FACS: deny mutation fallocate modes on append-only fds.
+	 * These modes mutate existing byte positions. */
+	if (mode & (FALLOC_FL_PUNCH_HOLE | FALLOC_FL_ZERO_RANGE |
+		    FALLOC_FL_COLLAPSE_RANGE | FALLOC_FL_INSERT_RANGE)) {
+		if (security_file_deny_pwrite(file))
+			return -EPERM;
+	}
+
